        "dimension": "logic_clarity",
        "related_files": [
          "src/toolkit/guards/pay-spend-cap.ts"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "Line 34: if (amount > policy.maxPerCall) return SPEND_LIMIT \u2014 fires before isFinite check",
          "Line 42: if (!Number.isFinite(amount) || amount <= 0) return INVALID_INPUT \u2014 second check",
          "If amount = -5: -5 > maxPerCall is false \u2192 passes line 34 \u2192 line 42 catches it (INVALID_INPUT). Correct result but wrong code path \u2014 the per-call max fires first.",
          "If amount = Infinity: Infinity > maxPerCall is true \u2192 returns SPEND_LIMIT. Correct by accident \u2014 but the real error is INVALID_INPUT (non-finite), not SPEND_LIMIT.",
          "Callers get SPEND_LIMIT for Infinity input, which suggests they should raise their maxSpend, not that the input is invalid."
        ],
        "suggestion": "Move the isFinite/positive check (lines 42-44) to before the maxPerCall check (line 34). Validate that amount is a valid number before comparing it against policy limits.",
        "reasoning": "",
        "summary_hash": "dd444c78"
      },
      "status": "open",
      "note": null,
      "first_seen": "2026-03-27T17:14:16+00:00",
